      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masaryktown%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town’s east‑west streets honor Slovak literary leaders like Štúr, Hurban, Kollár, Štefánik, Hodža, Hviezdoslav, and Mudron.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masaryktown%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "North‑south streets also commemorate U.S. presidents Wilson, Jefferson, Madison, and Lincoln, linking local history to national leaders.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masaryktown%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Masaryktown sits on Hernando County’s southern edge, bordered by Spring Hill to the north and Garden Grove to the northeast.",
